  "server": {
    "name": "io.nyc.dot",
    "title": "NYC Department of Transportation",
    "version": "0.1.0",
    "description": "Agent-native access to the NYC street network \u2014 bike routes, traffic & pedestrian signals, curbside parking regulations, speed humps, pedestrian plazas, bridges, and street-work permits. Unifies the DOT's 267 NYC Open Data assets around the LION street segment behind one owned surface; adds street-work permit applications.",
    "instructions": "Use find_bike_routes, find_traffic_signals, find_parking_regulations, find_speed_humps, find_plazas, and find_bridges to query street assets by borough, LION segmentId, and location. get_bridge / get_street_work_permit fetch a single record. find_street_work_permits searches issued street-opening permits; apply_street_work_permit (net-new) submits a NEW permit application \u2014 it requires an authenticated user and mutates state, so confirm all details with the user before submitting. Most assets share a LION segmentId, so you can pivot from one asset to another along the same blockface."
  },
